                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, March 14: The countrys foreign exchange reserves declined $1.98 billion to $247.29 billion for the week ended March 6 compared with $249.28 billion in the previous week. Reserves had fallen $249 million for the week ended February 27. During the week, foreign currency assets declined to $236.73 billion compared with $238.71 billion in the previous week, the Reserve Bank of India said in its weekly report.                             
	 Mumbai, March 14: The market regulator is considering the application of Multi-Commodity Exchange (MCX) to start a new segment for trading in equities and derivatives, Sebi chairman C.B. Bhave said.                             
	 Mumbai, March 14: Bajaj Auto has said its car project with Renault-Nissan was largely on schedule. Any financial or other constraints faced by Renault-Nissan will have no bearing on Bajajs ability to implement the project, it said.                                                                                                                           
